\'93Insects are the most numerous animals in both numbers of individuals and of different kinds, with more than a million species in all habitats except the sea, and they are of enormous economic importance as pests and carriers of disease, and also as pollinators.\'94\
\'93Stop!\'94 said Miles. He was shaking.\
